Requirements:

Degree or diploma holder in interior design, architecture or equivalent;
At least 3 years relevant experience in design and construction (office, retail, F&B & residential etc.);
Proficiency in AutoCAD / Sketch up / Photoshop / Enscape3D is a must;
Creative design concept, strong presentation and drawing skills are essential;
Take charge of delivering full set of interior design drawings, from concept, details, tender document to construction documents and relevant materials;
Partake in presentations and meetings to interpret design direction and requirements of projects;
Manages time and workload of own work efforts and those of others to meet project task deadlines and commitments, with occasional interaction and direction from team leaders while guiding and teaching less experienced staff, with leadership skill to lead design team to meet deadlines of projects in timely manner and assist design director to set out project goals and design directives;
Closely coordinate with stakeholders, such as end users, internal team members, senior management, contractors, suppliers, vendors and sub-contractors to ensure the project is executed smoothly;
Familiar with Hong Kong building regulations, and able to prepare interior drawings and tender sets would be an advantage;
Open-minded as well as having excellent communication and interpersonal skills and with high level of aesthetic flair;
Site experience and immediate availability is preferred;

Candidates with less experience in interior design will be considered as Assistant Interior Designer/ Draftsman.
We offer competitive package and promising career prospect to the right candidate.
Interested parties please send detailed resume, portfolio and expected salary quoting the corresponding position by clicking “Apply Now”.

Responsibilities

Prepare 2D technical CAD drawings, 3D knowledge is an advantage;
Independently handle full set of residential and commercial construction drawings;
Organise and prepare interior design presentation;
Follow up client's requirements and convert the leads into orders;
Build and enhance customer relationship;
Liaise with internal parties to maximise sales performance and smooth operations;
Assist in other ad-hoc assignments as required;
Direct report to Sales Director.
Requirements

Diploma / Associate / Bachelor of Interior Design or equivalent;
Good command in AutoCAD, Sketch up and common office software;
Good presentation and communication skills;
Customer-oriented and responsible;
Self-motivated, hardworking, organised, outgoing;
Able to work under pressure and independently;
5-day work week on roster is required, including weekends;
Able to standby anytime in responding to customers;
Good command of Cantonese, Mandarin and English;
Immediate available is preferred.

