Responsibilities:

Assist Associate Project Director in managing and planning proposals on Park Revamp, Connectivity Enhancement, Art Tech and Talent Nurturing Programs to ensure projects are accomplished within the planned schedule and budget as well as meeting the required quality and safety standards;
Oversee the improvement and minor works including term contracts, defects-rectification works, fitting out works, alteration and addition works;
Work closely with the project teams to produce preliminary and detailed designs, tender/construction documents, and to manage the procurement and construction process;
Handle the design drawing/graphics for presentation as well as tender and procurement documents for consultants selection/appointment by following up their subsequent management and monitoring their performance;
Liaison with various consultants, government departments, education institutions, park companies and relevant organizations on project planning, design and implementation as well as coordinate internally with Marketing Team, Clusters, Facility Management Team, Project Team on all related matters;
Responsible for the design management in coordination with end users (e.g. F&B tenants etc.), implementation and delivery of the approved strategies;   
Prepare papers and reports for seeking approval by the Board, Committees and Task Force of the Corporation;
Ensure compliance with the Corporation’s guidelines and Delegation Authority for capital works projects; and
Perform any other duties as assigned by supervisor.

Requirements:

A bachelor’s degree or above in Architecture, Interior Design, Surveying or related discipline;
Minimum 8 years’ relevant work experience with strong design and commercial sense in project management of building, interior design and A&A projects;
Proven connection with Hong Kong marketing / event organizers, F&B operators, etc.
Experience in managing projects from inception to completion including handover;
Experience in procuring and managing consultants, contract administration of large-scale projects, claim and EOT assessment as well as supervision of minor works contracts and term contracts;
Knowledge of statutory requirements and procedures for development projects in Hong Kong;
Conversant with graphics presentation tools. Skill on graphic software such as Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Illustrator, AutoCAD, Primavera, Microsoft Project, Revit and project management / design related computer application will be an advantage;
Self-driven, independent, problem solving with good interpersonal skill; and
Good command in both spoken and written English and Chinese. Proficiency in Putonghua will be an advantage.

Candidate with less experience will be considered for lower position.

We offer market competitive compensation, 5-day work week, and generous benefits including medical and life insurance; and voluntary contribution in addition to the legal minimum MPF.  To apply, please send your full resume with current and expected salary to the Human Resources & Office Administration Department, Hong Kong Science and Technology Parks Corporation, 5/F, Building 5E, 5 Science Park East Avenue, Hong Kong Science Park, Hong Kong or, by email via Apply Now" on or before 27 January 2022.   Please quote the reference number on the email subject/envelope and the application letter. 

Personal data provided will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment purpose only.  All personal data collected will be used strictly in accordance with employer’s personal data policies, you can access to HKSTP’s Personal Information Collection Statement at https://www.hkstp.org/hkstp_web/en/hkstp/personal-information-collection-statement-recruitment

Applicants not invited for interview within four weeks after application deadline may consider their applications unsuccessful.  Personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be retained for a maximum of two years. 

