To liaise with sub-contractors, vendors, production team and design team for project preparation;
Immediate available
Requirement:

Form 6 or above, diploma holder of business administration, project management or other related courses
2+ years solid experience in interior design or architectural firm or construction company is advantage;
Proficient knowledge in the Use of material and finishing, construction, supervise design and working drawing, and other related reports;
Able to handle clients, sub-contractors and vendor independently;
Presentable, proactive, self-initiative, independent, patient, multi-task skills and able to work overnight & under pressure;
Good command of written & spoken English and Mandarin
Good knowledge in MS office
Applicants with less than 1 year experience but with good potential will also be considered.
Interested parties please send full resume with date of availability, present & expected salary and portfolio to email by clicking "Apply Now".
If you do feel you possess the qualities we have mentioned above, and would like to work with a brilliant group of people, please do not hesitate to send us your full resume with present and expected salaries.
As an equal opportunity employer, we welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. Applicants not hearing from us within 4 weeks from the date of advertisement may consider their applications unsuccessful. All personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be treated in strict confidentiality and used for recruitment purposes only, and will be destroyed immediately upon completion of the recruitment exercise

